Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Kyasanur Forest disease (KFD) is caused by Kyasanur Forest disease virus (KFDV), which is transmitted to humans by a tick bite or contact with an infected animal, commonly a sick or recently dead monkey. No person-to-person transmission has been described to date (https://www.cdc.gov/vhf/kyasanur/transmission/index.html).

Recommended preventive measures against KFDV include vaccination of the at-risk population in the reported area and public education on use of insect repellents and protective clothing when outdoors or entering any nearby forests. - Mod.UBA

